    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-team-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level 3 due to single test condition; this gap is accepted given the deterministic nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and the close agreement observed across both laboratories. All three QoIs pass the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
